p: The VMN also delivered the highest tracheal dose (10.00 ± 0.67 %, distal at 5 LPM), (9.66 ± 1.51 %, distal at 11 LPM) and (12.06 ± 0.39 %, proximal at 5 LPM), (14.36 ± 1.25 %, proximal at 11 LPM) at both attachment setups and supplemental gas flow rates compared with the JN (3.73 ± 0.22 %, distal at 5 LPM) & (3.19 ± 0.69 %, distal at 11 LPM) and (7.79 ± 1.03 %, proximal at 5 LPM), (8.68 ± 0.39 %, proximal at 11 LPM).
